[[File:Sannozuka Kofun, funkyu and torii.jpg|thumb|right|250px|{{center|Sannozuka Kofun}}]]
{{Location map|Japan Saitama Prefecture|relief=1| lat_deg = 35| lat_min = 53| lat_sec = 59.4| lon_deg = 139| lon_min = 27| lon_sec = 42.5| label =Minami-Otsuka<br>Kofun Cluster| position = bottom| mark = Red pog.svg| marksize = 10| width = 250| caption={{Center|Location (showing the Sannozuka Kofun)}}}}

'''Minami-Otsuka Kofun Cluster''' (南大塚古墳群) is a cluster of kofun located in {{ill|Kawagoe, Saitama|ja|川越市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Saitama Prefecture|ja|埼玉県|12=draft}}. The cluster is bisected by the {{ill|Kan-etsu Expressway|ja|関越自動車道|12=draft}}. Thirteen kofun, including the {{ill|Sannozuka Kofun|ja|山王塚古墳|12=draft}}, remain. In 1969 (Shōwa 44), the site was designated an {{ill|Important Cultural Property|ja|埼玉県選定重要遺跡|12=draft}} by Saitama Prefecture. Among them, the Sannozuka Kofun was designated a [[National Historic Site of Japan]] on March 20, 2023.{{Sfn|Saitama Prefecture Board of Education|2022|pp=116–122}}{{Cite web|author=Kawagoe City Cultural Property Protection Division|url=https://www.city.kawagoe.saitama.jp/smph/kosodatekyoiku/kyoikuinkai/rekishi/oshirase/bunkazai041220.html|title=Sannozuka Kofun designated a National Historic Site|work=Kawagoe City|date=2023-03-20}}

== Main Kofun ==
=== Sannozuka Kofun ===
Located at the easternmost part of the cluster, the Sannozuka Kofun is a unique {{ill|Jōen-kahō-fun|ja|上円下方墳|1=Joenkahofun|12=draft}}. It was designated a Kawagoe City Historic Site in 1958 (Shōwa 33). The lower square section measures 63 meters per side and 1 meter in height, while the upper circular section has a diameter of 47 meters and a height of 3.5 meters. Excavations of the surrounding moat were conducted in 1991 (Heisei 3) and 1996 (Heisei 8).

=== Sannozuka West Kofun ===
This was a circular kofun approximately 32 meters in diameter, but it was destroyed during land reclamation in 1916 (Taishō 5). The burial chamber is a horizontally oriented stone chamber opening to the south, with a total length of 11.55 meters. Artifacts include:
* Weapons: Two swords, one pommel, various fittings, and fragments of iron arrowheads (22).
* Ornaments: Six agate magatama, two crystal magatama, one lacquered wooden bead, three small glass beads, 14 cylindrical glass beads, two cut crystal beads, nine gilt bronze rings, and five gilt bronze ring fragments.
These items were designated Kawagoe City Tangible Cultural Properties on February 24, 2010 (Heisei 22).

=== Sugawara Shrine East Kofun ===
[[File:Kawagoe_Sugawara_Zinzya_Haiden_1.jpg|thumb|Sugawara Shrine's hall, located atop Sugawara Shrine East Kofun]]
A circular kofun with a diameter of approximately 20 meters. The Sugawara Shrine hall was built atop the mound, leading to its deformation.{{Cite web|url=http://www.kawagoe-yell.com/sightseeing/look/minamiotuka-sugawara/|title=Minami-Otsuka Sugawara Shrine and East Kofun|publisher=Jukichi Co.|accessdate=2017-09-14}}

== Cultural Properties ==
=== National Designation ===
* Historic Site
''' Sannozuka Kofun: Designated a Kawagoe City Historic Site on March 6, 1958, and elevated to a National Historic Site on March 20, 2023.

=== Kawagoe City Designation ===
* Tangible Cultural Properties
''' Artifacts from Sannozuka West Kofun: Designated February 24, 2010.

